  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>To clarify this bug:

In mysite/profile/templates/profile/main.html , there are a few references to 
"&amp;rarr;", an HTML entity that draws a right-facing arrow.

Some time ago, we filed this bug because I thought it made sense to use "&amp;raquo;" 
instead; if you 'git grep raquo' you'll see that we use that much more often, and 
in other places on the site.

So in this bug, you will go and replace those "rarr"s with "raquo"s. Edit 
mysite/profile/templates/profile/main.html , make a local commit, and submit a 
pull request.

If you do this, you'll be fixing a bug that has been open for more than a year, 
which would be grand.

(Also: I'm marking this as bitesize, and would prefer that a new contributor to 
the project be the one to fix it.)</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
